From 3e94a70d83299a6d0af079fbf1bce3f4569270bf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: TBFS Security Review <review@tbfs.local>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 11:13:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 03/10] F-02/F-07/F-16/F-17: canonical RATES + shared payment
 waterfall in the engine
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- RATES object: every business rate (30% income table, 12% initiation,
  R60/R50/R45 admin, tier bounds/rates, 10% stockvel minimum, late
  penalty 0.1%/day cap 7) defined exactly once and exported. (F-07)
- allocateScheduledPayment(): pure shared waterfall in production order
  (initiation → admin → penalty → interest → principal) with interest-
  cap and principal clamps; replaces the dead allocatePayment(), whose
  loan.principal reference was NaN on real loans. (F-02/F-16)
- resolveScheduleStartYear(): first due month can never precede
  disbursement — fixes Dec-loan/Jan-start schedules landing a year in
  the past. getAdminFeeForContributions(): shared stockvel admin rule.
- calculateMembershipEndDate(): local-date formatting; toISOString()
  was shifting SAST dates back one day.
- Engine logging behind DEBUG (client figures no longer stream to the
  console) and window guard so Node tests can require() it. (F-17)
- tools/transform-calculations.mjs: the exact-match transform used,
  kept for audit.
